(23,'Q24. What is the operation doing given the Git commands below?\n\n```\ngit bisect start\ngit bisect bad 5d41402abc4b2a76b9719d911017c592\ngit bisect good 69faab6268350295550de7d587bc323d\n```\n',0,'It runs a merge of a good commit that is discovered using a known bad commit and known good commit',0,'It marks a commit for deletion using a known bad commit and known good commit to determine which commit introduced a bug',0,'It defines a bad commit and resets the HEAD using a known bad commit and known good commit',1,'It performs a binary search using a known bad commit and known good commit to determine which commit introduced a bug'),
