(104,'Q105. When Git Workflows contain a long-running branch, what purpose does the long-running branch serve?',0,'Long-running branches store unstable code until it os peer reviewed for integration into a feature branch.',0,'Long-running branches correspond to agile sprints and are used to store related to features developed in the sprint.',0,'Long-running branches contain code related to experimental feature development that is merged into short-lived branches such as master.',1,'Long-running branches correspond to different stages of development and are always open for topic/feature branches to be pulled into.'),
